        "## 9.12 Linearization as a local model in statistics and machine learning\n",
        "\n",
        "Many statistical and machine-learning models depend on parameters. A simple example is a two-parameter linear prediction model\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\hat y=\\beta_0+\\beta_1x.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "A more complicated model may have many parameters:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\hat y=f(x;\\theta_1,\\theta_2,\\ldots,\\theta_n).\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Near a parameter vector $\\boldsymbol\\theta_0$, linear approximation gives\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "f(x;\\boldsymbol\\theta)\\approx f(x;\\boldsymbol\\theta_0)+\\nabla_{\\boldsymbol\\theta}f(x;\\boldsymbol\\theta_0)\\cdot (\\boldsymbol\\theta-\\boldsymbol\\theta_0).\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "This is the local linear model used in:\n",
        "\n",
        "- sensitivity analysis of model outputs;\n",
        "- uncertainty propagation for estimated parameters;\n",
        "- first-order optimization methods;\n",
        "- local approximation of nonlinear regression models;\n",
        "- gradient-based learning in neural networks.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Local linearization of a sigmoid\n",
        "\n",
        "The logistic sigmoid is\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\sigma(t)=\\frac{1}{1+e^{-t}}.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "If\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "t=\\beta_0+\\beta_1x,\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "then the model output is\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "p(x;\\beta_0,\\beta_1)=\\sigma(\\beta_0+\\beta_1x).\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "For fixed $x$, this is a function of the parameters $\\beta_0$ and $\\beta_1$. Its gradient tells how the predicted probability changes when the parameters change."
      ],
      "id": "ccecc86e"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "fig-width": 7,
        "fig-height": 5
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: fig-ch09-logistic-local-linearization\n",
        "#| fig-cap: A nonlinear probability model is locally approximated by its tangent plane in parameter space.\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "x0 = 1.5\n",
        "b0_star, b1_star = -0.4, 1.2\n",
        "\n",
        "def sigmoid(t):\n",
        "    return 1/(1 + np.exp(-t))\n",
        "\n",
        "b0 = np.linspace(-1.2, 0.4, 140)\n",
        "b1 = np.linspace(0.4, 2.0, 140)\n",
        "B0, B1 = np.meshgrid(b0, b1)\n",
        "P = sigmoid(B0 + B1*x0)\n",
        "\n",
        "p0 = sigmoid(b0_star + b1_star*x0)\n",
        "deriv = p0*(1 - p0)\n",
        "dp_db0 = deriv\n",
        "dp_db1 = deriv*x0\n",
        "L = p0 + dp_db0*(B0 - b0_star) + dp_db1*(B1 - b1_star)\n",
        "\n",
        "fig = plt.figure()\n",
        "ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')\n",
        "ax.plot_surface(B0, B1, P, alpha=0.65, linewidth=0)\n",
        "ax.plot_surface(B0, B1, L, alpha=0.35, linewidth=0)\n",
        "ax.scatter([b0_star], [b1_star], [p0], s=60)\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel(r'$\\beta_0$')\n",
        "ax.set_ylabel(r'$\\beta_1$')\n",
        "ax.set_zlabel('probability')\n",
        "ax.set_title('Local linearization of logistic probability')\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "fig-ch09-logistic-local-linearization",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
